<h1>29. A stroll around Pwll-yr-Wrach Nature Reserve</h1>
<div class="article-video right clearfix"/>
<p/><div>
<span style="color: rgb(105, 105, 105);"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif;">An easy access trail with hard surface gently winds its way 550 yards/500 metres down into the heart of the woodland valley and River Enig.</span></span></span><br/>
<br/>
<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 0);"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Further information</strong></span></span></span><br/>
<br/>
<span style="color: rgb(105, 105, 105);"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif;">This nature reserve is owned and managed by Brecknock Wildlife Trust and is home to a range of wildlife, trees, flowers and ferns. The main path has a single handrail, resting spots and passing places. Unsurfaced compacted earth paths continue further into the reserve and to the witches pool or â€˜pwll yr wrachâ€™. There are information boards on the local wildlife and geology of the area and guided walks are organised by the Wildlife Trust. A leaflet is available from the Wildlife Trust.</span></span></span><br/>
<br/>
<br/>
<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 0);"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>How to get there:</strong></span></span></span><span style="color: rgb(105, 105, 105);"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif;">This reserve is on a minor road about 1 mile south of Talgarth, 500 metres past the former Mid Wales Hospital.</span></span></span><br/>
<br/>
<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 0);"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Nearest town or village:</strong></span></span></span><span style="color: rgb(105, 105, 105);"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif;">Talgarth.</span></span></span><br/>
<br/>
<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 0);"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>OS Grid Reference:</strong></span></span></span><span style="color: rgb(105, 105, 105);"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif;">Explorer Map OL 13 or Landranger Map 161 - SO 162 328.</span></span></span><br/>
<br/>
<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 0);"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Distance:</strong></span></span></span><span style="color: rgb(105, 105, 105);"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif;">500 metres to the valley bottom, with a further 1km of uneven earth paths.</span></span></span><br/>
<br/>
<span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong><span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 0);">Contact:</span></strong><span style="color: rgb(105, 105, 105);">Brecknock Wildlife Trust on 01874 625708.</span><br/>
<br/>
<strong><span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 0);">Facilities:</span></strong><span style="color: rgb(105, 105, 105);">The closest shops, seasonal information centre and services are in Talgarth.</span><br/>
<br/>
<strong><span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 0);">Parking:</span></strong></span></span><span style="color: rgb(105, 105, 105);"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif;">There is a small compacted stone-dust car park by the roadside.</span></span></span><br/>
<br/>
<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 0);"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Toilets:</strong></span></span></span><span style="color: rgb(105, 105, 105);"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,helvetica,sans-serif;">The nearest toilets are in Talgarth opposite the Co-op.</span></span></span></div>

